'''Buddha Lama''' (born November 23, 1997) is Nepalese singer, actor and model who rose to fame after winning the title and becoming the first winner of Nepalese TV series ''[[Nepal Idol]]''. Since winning ''Nepal Idol'', he has become a [[teen idol]]. Lama holds the title for ''Nepal Idol'' winner for the season one with Nishan Bhattarai as runner up and Partap Das as second runner up.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.myrepublica.com/news/28046/|title=Buddha Lama clinches Nepal Idol title|work=My Republica|access-date=2017-10-04|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kathmandutribune.com/buddha-lama-is-the-winner-nepal-idol/|title=Buddha Lama is the winner of Nepal Idol – Kathmandu Tribune – Nepal's Online Daily {{!}} Latest News from Nepal and the world|last=Tribune|first=Kathmandu|date=2017-09-23|work=Kathmandu Tribune – Nepal's Online Daily {{!}} Latest News from Nepal and the world|access-date=2017-10-04|language=en-US}}</ref>

== Career ==

=== ''Nepal Idol'' success ===
Lama participated in Nepalese reality television show ''[[Nepal Idol]]'' and he managed to win the show with the prize of Pranish, 20 &nbsp;Lakhs NPR, album and contract worth of 15 &nbsp;Lakhs. After winning ''Nepal Idol'', he went to the Nepal Idol Worldwide Tour with [[Nishan Bhattarai]] and Pratap Das.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/news/2017-11-05/nepal-idols-on-a-uk-tour.html|title=Nepal Idols on a UK tour|access-date=2017-11-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kathmandutribune.com/nepal-idol-usa-tour-2018/|title=Nepal Idol USA Tour 2018 – Kathmandu Tribune – Nepal's National Online Daily|date=2017-11-18|work=Kathmandu Tribune – Nepal's National Online Daily|access-date=2017-11-26|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.myrepublica.com/news/30790/?categoryId=81|title=OPPO lifts the wraps off OPPO F5|work=My Republica|access-date=2017-11-26|language=en}}</ref> He was also in limelight due to his row with the organizers regarding the prize money.

