{{Infobox journal | title = International Journal of Productivity and Performance Management | cover = | editor = Thomas F. Burgess, John Heap | discipline = [[Performance management]] and [[Performance measurement|measurement]] | former_names = Work Study | abbreviation = Int. J. Prod. Perform. Manag. | publisher = [[Emerald Group Publishing]] | country = | frequency = 8/year | history = 1952-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.emeraldinsight.com/products/journals/journals.htm?id=ijppm | link1 = http://www.emeraldinsight.com/journals.htm?issn=1741-0401 | link1-name = Online access | ISSN = 1741-0401 | eISSN = | OCLC = 54312680 | LCCN = 2005204237 }} The '''''International Journal of Productivity and Performance Management''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[performance management]] and [[Performance measurement|measurement]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Thomas F. Burgess ([[Leeds University Business School]]) and John Heap ([[National Productivity Centre]]). The journal was established in 1952 and is published by [[Emerald Group Publishing]]. It is the official journal of the [[World Confederation of Productivity Science]]. The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[ABI/Inform]], [[Inspec]], [[ProQuest|ProQuest databases]], [[PsycINFO]], and [[Scopus]].
